br.fml.eti.machinegun.auditorship
Interface ArmyAudit

All Known Implementing Classes:
NegligentAuditor
public interface ArmyAudit

Almost everything that happens in Army is reported here, don't worry. Irrelevant things will not be reported due these things are internal implementations with constant time, as the internal buffer consumers, e.g.

It is useful if you need to log and/or measure the time of the main operations.

updateCurrentBufferSize

void updateCurrentBufferSize(int newSize,
                             int maxSize)
If newSize / maxSize is near to 100%, it means that the internal buffer is overloaded and a call to MachineGun.fire(T, java.lang.String) can block for a while.

Parameters:
newSize - Elements into an internal buffer to be consumed.
maxSize - Maximum capacity of the internal buffer.
